Uses of Package
agents.org.apache.commons.math

  • Packages that use agents.org.apache.commons.math 
    Package Description
    agents.org.apache.commons.math
    Common classes used throughout the commons-math library.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.analysis
    Parent package for common numerical analysis procedures, including root finding, function interpolation and integration.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.analysis.integration
    Numerical integration (quadrature) algorithms for univariate real functions.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.analysis.interpolation
    Univariate real functions interpolation algorithms.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.analysis.polynomials
    Univariate real polynomials implementations, seen as differentiable univariate real functions.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.analysis.solvers
    Root finding algorithms, for univariate real functions.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.complex
    Complex number type and implementations of complex transcendental functions.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.dfp
    Decimal floating point library for Java
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.distribution
    Implementations of common discrete and continuous distributions.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.estimation
    This package provided classes to solve estimation problems, it is deprecated since 2.0.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.fraction
    Fraction number type and fraction number formatting.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.geometry
    This package provides basic 3D geometry components.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.linear
    Linear algebra support.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.ode
    This package provides classes to solve Ordinary Differential Equations problems.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.ode.events
    This package provides classes to handle discrete events occurring during Ordinary Differential Equations integration.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.optimization
    This package provides common interfaces for the optimization algorithms provided in sub-packages.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.optimization.direct
    This package provides optimization algorithms that don't require derivatives.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.optimization.fitting
    This package provides classes to perform curve fitting.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.optimization.general
    This package provides optimization algorithms that require derivatives.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.optimization.linear
    This package provides optimization algorithms for linear constrained problems.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.optimization.univariate
    Univariate real functions minimum finding algorithms.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.random
    Random number and random data generators.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.special
    Implementations of special functions such as Beta and Gamma.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.stat.correlation
    Correlations/Covariance computations.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.stat.descriptive
    Generic univariate summary statistic objects.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.stat.descriptive.moment
    Summary statistics based on moments.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.stat.inference
    Classes providing hypothesis testing and confidence interval construction.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.stat.regression
    Statistical routines involving multivariate data.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.transform
    Implementations of transform methods, including Fast Fourier transforms.
    agents.org.apache.commons.math.util
    Convenience routines and common data structures used throughout the commons-math library.
  • Classes in agents.org.apache.commons.math used by agents.org.apache.commons.math 
    Class and Description
    ConvergenceException
    Error thrown when a numerical computation can not be performed because the numerical result failed to converge to a finite value.
    ConvergingAlgorithm
    Deprecated. 
    in 2.2 (to be removed in 3.0). The concept of "iteration" will be moved to a new IterativeAlgorithm. The concept of "accuracy" is currently is also contained in SimpleRealPointChecker and similar classes.

    Interface representing a field.
    FunctionEvaluationException
    Exception thrown when an error occurs evaluating a function.
    MathException
    Base class for commons-math checked exceptions.
